table543

Yes, it works and it's very easy. But be careful: if your Vista is 32 bits and you want to install Windows 7 64 bits, it's impossible...and I think it's the same problem from 64 to 32 bits.

I did an upgrade from Vista 32 bits to Windows 7 32 bits without any problem.

Your computer may be too old and your processor isn't compatible with 64 bits applications: this version of Windows 7 is only for 64 bits processors.
